To create a file using vi --> vi filename
To insert a line in the file using vi --> press i (after running vi filename command)
To save and quit from the vi editor to linux terminal ---> Esc+: then press wq! (It will save the content written in the file and quit to get back to the linux terminal)
To move (left,right,up and down to the vi editor) using the short cut keys---> after entering in vi editor to move right use 'l' key, 
                                                                                                           to move left use 'h' key, 
                                                                                                           to move up use 'k' key, 
                                                                                                           to move down use 'j' key
To view the contents in file : cat filename
To view the contents along with line number : cat -b filename
To view the total word count along with other details : wc filename (where 1st column shows total word count
                                                                           2nd column shows total line count
                                                                           3rd column shows total size in bytes of the file
                                                                           4th column shows filename)
